  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7  \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dad\u0ddc\u0d9c \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cipetco filling stations do not have enough stock",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kapila Naotunna, Joint Secretary of the Petroleum Separators Association, said today (28) afternoon that the fuel stock provided by the Petroleum Corporation Cipetco filling stations is not sufficient at all and due to this the fuel crisis has worsened due to people waiting in queues.",
        "Mr. Naotunna mentioned that Cipetco petrol stations only get a small stock of fuel once or twice a week and that stock is not enough to supply the people in queues.",
        "Mr. Kei Naotunna said that IOC petrol stations receive at least four stocks of fuel per week and noted that the 1200 Sipetco petrol stations nationwide and hundreds of thousands of people are suffering from this situation.",
        "Mr. Naotunna further stated that no matter what method the Ministry of Energy adopts, no method will be successful if there is no fuel stock."
      ],
